Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Cross River State,  John Ochala, has called on President Muhammadu Buhari to reward faithful and loyal members of the party. Ochala, who spoke in Calabar, said, “I urge that under the next level dispensation of Mr. President, there should be recourse to rewarding loyalty, steadfastness and resoluteness of party men and women.” “I want all party members to be resolute, steadfast and never give up as the fulfillment of our collective destinies as a state lies solely in the hands of members through the gospel of change.” Minister, aides have no power to control C’River APC, says chairman P16 for editing p16 OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY